# React Compiler

The project uses React Compiler (babel-plugin-react-compiler). The compiler automatically optimizes React components, so manual memoization with `useMemo`, `useCallback`, and `React.memo` is generally not needed unless there are specific performance issues that require it.

# "libs" projects

When you change code in "/libs" you need to run `pnpm install` to update the dependencies for "apps/"" and no need to run `pnpm build` for any "/libs"

